title: Corbyn pulls out of TV interviews because he's 'tired'
text:
Jeremy Corbyn was due to be interviewed by ITV News today Credit: PA The Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn has pulled out of interviews with the ITV regions scheduled for today because he is "too tired and losing his voice".
ITV's Political Correspondent Paul Brand has the latest:
Paul Brand @PaulBrandITV Follow Corbyn has pulled out of interviews with ITV regions. Too tired and losing voice. Yesterday he said we must hold politicians to account.
09:36 - 30 Sep 2015 Retweet Reply Favourite Paul Brand @PaulBrandITV Follow Cameraman who's been doing these interviews for ITV since 1991 can't remember a time a party leader pulled out. Corbyn a first.
